This is a lower budget 3d kids film.  The 3d is good but the animation is not the greatest. But it's good enough for a good watch and the 3d adds to it. this does have the flat version , which is half the film of the 3d one.  it features good voice acting , from b list actors.  Obviously this is a low budget affair  and so you can't expect high quality animation, but it's not terrible and this is a low priced item, so no complaints from me. I would say that all animated films really can benefit from a 3d release.  And this one was filmed that way , so 3d collectors should want this one in their collection.  It's a fine kids film featuring talking animals.  So your kids should enjoy it too.

2-stars is the fairest rating.  Manu is a coati.  I thought it was a type of monkey, but it's a relative of the raccoon that lives in Central & South America.  He by his nature gets into trouble and gets exiled.  Sacha, also a coati, is his friend/sorta girlfriend and also princess of the tribe.  She goes looking for Manu and is captured by poachers.  The story goes on from there and has a moral of accepting others as they are.

Pro's:  Eh, It wasn't horrible.

Cons:  The cheap looking animation style.
  The really simplistic dialog of the script.
